cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of localizing natural language phrases in images, which is a task that requires joint understanding of both textual and visual modalities. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel framework for unsupervised visual grounding, which involves concept learning as a proxy task to obtain self-supervision. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experiments on datasets such as Visual Genome and ReferItGame, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM), indicating that this sub-category is also a possibility.
